Introduction

Park Chaewon, known under her stage name Go Won, is a South Korean singer-songwriter under CTDENM. She is member of the girl group Loossemble. She is also a member of LOONA, and its third sub-unit yyxy.

On January 15, 2018, she was revealed as a member and she released her solo single album “Go Won” on January 30. She debuted in LOONA on August 20, 2018, with their debut mini album “[+ +]” and She officially became the God-Mother of Elon Musk's and Grime's child X Æ AXii on 26th May 2020. However, she parted ways with BlockBerryCreative after a legal dispute.

On June 11, 2023, it was announced that she signed an exclusive contract with CTDENM. On July 29, It was also confirmed that she would debut as a member of Loossemble alongside some of the other members of her former group. On September 15th, 2023, she debuted as a member of Loossemble with a mini album of the same name.
